{"source_key":"sha256-c8597aca71664a84bdd657ea13dadbd3","record_index":1012,"record_hash":"sha256:80e46c659118fde1fd5e3a778384f996d8e8e5a143bdcff1750e06cbf195f11b","timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:20:06.830Z","kind":"tool_call","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:custom_tool_call","role":null,"text":null,"tool_name":"apply_patch","tool_input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: /Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 [REDACTED:entropy].md\n@@\n-For this use case, turns are more valuable than whole-session links because a\n-session may span unrelated work. A review view can start from a branch, change,\n-commit, or PR, find related sessions, and then use turn evidence to highlight\n-the likely relevant parts of those sessions.\n+For this use case, turns are more valuable than whole-session links because a\n+session may span unrelated work. A review view can start from a branch, change,\n+or PR, find related sessions, and then use turn evidence to highlight the likely\n+relevant parts of those sessions. Commit-centric lookup can come later by\n+resolving through change or branch evidence; it does not need its own v1 index.\n@@\n-Turn identity should be derived from capture content, not from time or provider\n-turn ids:\n+Turn identity should be derived from capture content, not from time or provider\n+turn ids. Use a 128-bit truncated SHA-256 value: take the first 16 bytes of the\n+digest and render them as 32 lowercase hex characters.\n \n ```text\n-turn-key = sha256-hex16(session_key + NUL + source_key + NUL + ordered_new_record_hashes)\n+turn-key = sha256-trunc128(session_key + NUL + source_key + NUL + ordered_new_record_hashes)\n ```\n@@\n The first hook run for a session may capture more than one actual conversation\n turn if it imports an existing transcript backlog. Later stop-hook runs should\n usually map more closely to one user/agent interaction. That distinction should\n stay visible in the model: a turn is a capture observation, not necessarily a\n provider-native turn.\n \n For first-time backfill, create one capture turn containing all newly written\n records and one environment snapshot from capture time. Provider-native turn\n identifiers, when available, can be preserved as optional record-level grouping\n metadata, but they should not become real session turns during backfill because\n historical repository environment snapshots cannot be reconstructed.\n+\n+Store a compact `capture_kind` on the turn:\n+\n+- `backfill`: the capture imported an existing transcript backlog\n+- `incremental`: the capture observed new records from an ongoing session\n+\n+Backfill turns are valid transcript history, but their environment snapshot is\n+weaker association evidence because it only describes capture time, not the time\n+each historical provider turn happened.\n@@\n - source key\n+- capture kind\n - capture timestamp\n@@\n Implementation should write transcript records, record hashes, the turn object,\n the turn list entry, and derived index entries as one logical GitMeta update.\n If transcript record writes can succeed while the turn write fails, a later\n retry may see zero new records and skip the missing turn.\n+\n+Capture should also have a simple concurrency rule. Either hold a repo/session\n+capture lock around dedupe, previous-turn lookup, and write, or use optimistic\n+retry if the record-hash set or latest turn summary changes before the atomic\n+write. `previous_turn_key` means \"the latest committed capture turn in this\n+session immediately before this turn was written.\" Concurrent captures must not\n+silently create two turns that both claim the same previous turn unless their\n+record sets really are independent retries of the same observation.\n@@\n Candidate fields:\n \n - uncommitted worktree files: all tracked and untracked files with uncommitted\n@@\n - optional change id for each commit\n - files changed by each commit\n+\n+Also store a compact `observed_targets` summary on the turn detail. It should\n+contain the canonical branch, review, and change keys that were indexed for this\n+turn. This keeps candidate verification and future index rebuilds cheap without\n+duplicating the whole environment snapshot in every reader.\n@@\n Branch names, relative file paths, review identifiers, change ids, commit ids,\n and commit file lists are acceptable for repo-scoped `gitbutler:*` metadata\n@@\n access, such as selected web review links.\n+\n+Canonical target keys should be defined before writing indexes:\n+\n+- branch key material: normalized full refname when available, with display name\n+  kept separately for UI\n+- review key material: provider plus repo-scoped review identity, for example\n+  `github-pr:owner/repo#1284` when the owner/repo is available\n+- change key material: `gitbutler-change:<change-id>`\n+\n+Hash branch and review key material before embedding it in GitMeta key names if\n+escaping rules or key length are awkward. Keep the readable canonical value in\n+`observed_targets` and the environment snapshot.\n@@\n Commit file lists should use the same pattern:\n@@\n }\n ```\n+\n+Cap the number of commits recorded per branch as well. V1 should use a simple\n+limit such as 100 commits per branch and store `commit_count` plus\n+`commits_truncated` on the branch snapshot. That avoids a pathological branch\n+turning one capture into a giant metadata write.\n@@\n Concrete turn detail example:\n \n ```json\n {\n   \"schema\": \"gitbutler.agent-session-turn.v1\",\n-  \"turn_key\": \"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\n-  \"session_key\": \"sha256-1122334455667788\",\n-  \"source_key\": \"sha256-9988776655443322\",\n-  \"previous_turn_key\": \"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\n+  \"turn_key\": \"sha256-a1b2c3d4e5f60718aabbccddeeff0011\",\n+  \"session_key\": \"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\n+  \"source_key\": \"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\n+  \"previous_turn_key\": \"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\n+  \"capture_kind\": \"incremental\",\n   \"captured_at\": \"2026-05-20T18:42:11.123Z\",\n   \"records\": [\n@@\n       \"record_hash\": \"sha256:abc123...\"\n     }\n   ],\n+  \"observed_targets\": {\n+    \"branches\": [\n+      {\n+        \"key\": \"branch:refs/heads/agentlog-turns\",\n+        \"name\": \"agentlog-turns\"\n+      }\n+    ],\n+    \"reviews\": [\n+      {\n+        \"key\": \"github-pr:owner/repo#1284\",\n+        \"provider\": \"github\",\n+        \"pull_request\": 1284\n+      }\n+    ],\n+    \"changes\": [\n+      {\n+        \"key\": \"gitbutler-change:[REDACTED:entropy]\",\n+        \"change_id\": \"[REDACTED:entropy]\"\n+      }\n+    ]\n+  },\n   \"environment\": {\n@@\n         \"branches\": [\n           {\n+            \"key\": \"branch:refs/heads/agentlog-turns\",\n             \"name\": \"agentlog-turns\",\n             \"review\": {\n+              \"key\": \"github-pr:owner/repo#1284\",\n+              \"provider\": \"github\",\n               \"pull_request\": 1284,\n               \"review_id\": null\n             },\n+            \"commit_count\": 1,\n+            \"commits_truncated\": false,\n             \"commits\": [\n               {\n                 \"commit_id\": \"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:20:06.830Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}